---
import BaseLayout from "../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="pg_tviews - Incremental Materialized Views | FraiseQL"
  description="Transactional materialized view refreshes in PostgreSQL. 2,083× faster than full rebuilds. ACID-compliant incremental updates."
>
  <div style="padding: 2rem; max-width: 1280px; margin: 0 auto;">
    <h1>📊 pg_tviews</h1>
    <p style="font-size: 1.2rem; color: #666;">
      <strong>Incremental Materialized Views</strong> – Fast JSONB aggregations
    </p>

    <section style="margin: 2rem 0;">
      <h2>What It Does</h2>
      <p>
        pg_tviews adds transactional materialized view (tv_*) support to
        PostgreSQL with incremental refresh.
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>2,083× faster refreshes</strong> vs full rebuild
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Incremental updates</strong>: Only recalculate changed data
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>ACID transactions</strong>: 2PC consistency guarantee
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>JSONB output</strong>: Pre-computed aggregations as JSON
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Zero downtime</strong>: Readers see consistent snapshot
        </li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section style="margin: 2rem 0;">
      <h2>Why It Exists</h2>
      <p>
        PostgreSQL materialized views are expensive to refresh—full rebuilds
        block readers:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>Full refresh required on any change</li>
        <li>View locked during rebuild</li>
        <li>Expensive for large datasets</li>
        <li>No incremental update mechanism</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        pg_tviews solves this with PostgreSQL 14+ dynamic views and Rust-side
        coordination.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section style="margin: 2rem 0;">
      <h2>Key Features</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>Incremental Refresh</strong>: Only recompute affected rows
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>JSONB Aggregation</strong>: Pre-compute JSON responses
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>2PC Support</strong>: Distributed transaction consistency
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Snapshot Isolation</strong>: Readers never see locks
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Automatic Triggering</strong>: On source table changes
        </li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section style="margin: 2rem 0;">
      <h2>Performance</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>Refresh time</strong>: 2,083× faster than full rebuild
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Memory footprint</strong>: Constant regardless of data growth
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Reader latency</strong>: Zero impact (no locks)
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Query response time</strong>: O(1) on materialized results
        </li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section style="margin: 2rem 0;">
      <h2>Technology Stack</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>Language</strong>: SQL + Rust (coordination)
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Database</strong>: PostgreSQL 14+ (dynamic views)
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Output Format</strong>: JSONB (native PostgreSQL type)
        </li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section style="margin: 2rem 0;">
      <h2>Integration with Other Tools</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>fraiseql</strong>: Automatically uses tv_* tables for read
          optimization
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>CQRS pattern</strong>: Implements query side of CQRS
        </li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section style="margin: 2rem 0;">
      <h2>Quick Start</h2>
      <pre><code>-- Define materialized view
CREATE TABLE tv_user_stats AS (
  SELECT
    user_id,
    to_jsonb(row_to_json(agg)) as data
  FROM (
    SELECT user_id, COUNT(*) as order_count, SUM(total) as lifetime_value
    FROM orders
    GROUP BY user_id
  ) agg
);

-- fraiseql automatically uses tv_user_stats for user.stats queries</code></pre>
    </section>

    <section style="margin: 2rem 0;">
      <h2>GitHub Repository</h2>
      <p>
        <a href="https://github.com/fraiseql/pg_tviews" target="_blank">
          Visit pg_tviews on GitHub →
        </a>
      </p>
    </section>

    <section style="margin: 2rem 0;">
      <h2>Related Tools</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><a href="/ecosystem/fraiseql-core">fraiseql</a> – Core engine</li>
        <li><a href="/ecosystem">← Back to Ecosystem</a></li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <p style="margin-top: 2rem;">
      <a href="/">← Back to Home</a>
    </p>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
